Citation.sAbstract: Experimental densities,  , and refractive indices, nD for binary liquid mixtures of benzene with triethylamine (TEA) and tributylamine (TBA) have been measured as a function of composition in the temperature range from 278.15 to 318.15 K. The excess molar volume, VE, and its temperature dependence, dVE/dT for the binary mixtures were calculated using the experimental data. The values of VE for the mixtures were also estimated by using the Flory statistical theory and refractive index.
Citation.sTitle: Densities and Refractive Indices of Binary Mixtures of Benzene with Triethylamine and Tributylamine at Different Temperatures
